  <recipe id="Kir Royale">
    <head>
      <title>Kir Royale</title>
      <categories>
        <cat class="main">Drinks</cat>
        <cat class="diet">Egg-free</cat>
				<cat class="diet">Nut-free</cat>
      </categories>
    </head>
    <description><xhtml:p>My Lieblingsgetr&#228;nke. My Tante Heidi introduced me to these when I lived with her and Onkel Ernst while working for IBM. Often, Heidi and I would finish a bottle of champagne together, then I would carefully walk down the two flights of winding stairs to my room on the ground floor.</xhtml:p></description>
    <ingredients system="US">
      <ing-div>
        <ing>
          <item>One bottle of sparkling wine</item>
<!--One bottle of sparkling wine-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <item>Creme de cassis</item>
<!--Creme de cassis-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <item>Champagne flutes</item>
          <prep>the more narrow the better</prep>
<!--Champagne flutes, the more narrow the better-->
        </ing>
      </ing-div>
    </ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>In each champagne flute, fill one-third with creme de cassis. Top with sparkling wine.</step>
      <step>One bottle of sparkling wine will make six to eight kir royale.</step>
      <step>Substitue white wine for the sparking wine for a kir.</step>
    </directions>
  </recipe>
